summary: This is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system, approving travel for an FBI agent to conduct a witness interview in Los Angeles as part of the Epstein investigation. The email indicates the trip was scheduled for December 2019 and was pending further approval in April 2020.

events.title: Scheduled Witness Interview Trip
events.description: Travel authorization for an FBI agent to travel to Los Angeles, CA to conduct a witness interview as part of the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The document is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system dated April 16, 2020.
It approves travel for an FBI agent to Los Angeles for a witness interview related to the Epstein investigation.
The scheduled trip dates were December 15-18, 2019, indicating ongoing investigative activity after Epstein's death.
The travel authorization was pending further approval as of April 2020.
The document shows the DOJ was actively investigating Epstein-related matters in late 2019/early 2020.
